      DependencyIndex: 11
      LevelID: 3
      NodeType: 3
      Ports:
        Description:
          String: ""
        DescriptionText:
          ClassType1: TEXT
          String: |-
            Post Effect graph,  a simple gaussian kernel to reduce image noise and detail. 
            
            Blur Factor settings can be adjusted to control the blur amount. For this subgraph to work properly, Pixel Size and TexCoords must be connected, and Mipmaps must be enabled for the texture on the material.
            
            Tip:
            You can enable Expose Size Out in the Texture 2D Object Parameter node and connect it to the Gaussian Blur's Pixel Size, as well as TexCoords to Screen UV coords.
        FirstTime:
          Variable: false
        Locked:
          Variable: false
        SubGraphUniqueID10:
          Connection0:
            NodeLevelID: 1
            PortID: ScreenCoord
          Variable: [0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0]
        SubGraphUniqueID13:
          IOType: 1
          Variable: [0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0]
        SubGraphUniqueID5:
